name: County
requirementHigh: 2 sub-components with the same classification or higher;1 sub-component with a higher classification;classified as alert or emergency if nutrition or mortality is an alert or emergency
requirementLow: 2 sub-components with the same classification or higher
emergencyHigh: Nutrition OR Mortality = Emergency;2 sub-components = Emergency
alertHigh: Nutrition OR Mortality = Alert;1 sub-component = Emergency;2 sub-components = Alert

name: Food Security & Livelihoods
requirementHigh: 2 sub-components with the same classification or higher;1 sub-component with a higher classification
requirementLow: 2 sub-components with the same classification or higher

name: Food Availability & Access
requirementHigh: 3 indicators with the same classification or higher;2 indicators with a higher classification;classified as an emergency if household hunger score is an emergency
requirementLow: 3 indicators with the same classification or higher;2 indicators with a higher classification
emergencyHigh: Household Hunger Score = Emergency;3 indicators = Emergency

name: Livelihoods
requirementHigh: 2 sub-components with the same classification or higher;1 sub-component with a classification 2 levels higher
requirementLow: 2 sub-components with the same classification or higher;1 sub-component with a classification 2 levels higher

name: Agriculture
requirementHigh: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher;1 indicator with a higher classification;not classified if agriculture is not a key aspect of the livelihood zone
requirementLow: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher;1 indicator with a higher classification;not classified if agriculture is not a key aspect of the livelihood zone

name: Livestock
requirementHigh: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher;1 indicator with a higher classification;not classified if livestock is not a key aspect of the livelihood zone
requirementLow: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher;1 indicator with a classification 2 levels higher;not classified if livestock is not a key aspect of the livelihood zone

name: Markets
requirementHigh: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher (3 are required for an emergency classification);1 indicator with a higher classification;not classified if markets are not a key aspect of the livelihood zone
requirementLow: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher (3 are required for an emergency classification);1 indicator with a higher classification;not classified if markets are not a key aspect of the livelihood zone

name: Climate
requirementHigh: 1 indicator with the same classification or higher
requirementLow: 1 indicator with the same classification or higher

name: Coping
requirementHigh: 1 indicator with the same classification or higher

name: Water Sanitation & Hygiene
requirementHigh: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher;1 indicator with a higher classification;classified as an emergency if cholera score is an emergency
requirementLow: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher;classified as an emergency if cholera score is an emergency

name: Health
requirementHigh: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher;1 indicator with a higher classification;classified as an emergency if cholera or ebola score is an emergency
requirementLow: 2 indicators with the same classification or higher;1 indicator with a higher classification;classified as an emergency if cholera or ebola score is an emergency
emergencyHigh: Cholera OR Ebola = Emergency;2 indicators = Emergency
emergencyLow: Cholera OR Ebola = Emergency;2 indicators = Emergency

name: Nutrition
requirementHigh: 1 indicator with the same classification or higher
requirementLow: 1 indicator with the same classification or higher

name: Mortality
requirementHigh: 1 indicator with the same classification or higher
requirementLow: 1 indicator with the same classification or higher
